# RACommons.rag.exports
#
# Backend-conditional exports for the RAG pipeline. Appended to the main
# RACommons.exports list only when CMake is built with -DRAC_BACKEND_RAG=ON
# (the default on every target except Emscripten, where the onnxruntime-wasm
# vendor dep is gated). When RAG is OFF, the rac_rag_*_proto and
# rac_backend_rag_* symbols do not exist in librac_commons, so listing them
# in the unconditional exports list would make the Apple `-exported_symbols_list`
# linker reject the entire export contract with `Undefined symbol`.
#
# See sdk/runanywhere-commons/CMakeLists.txt — the conditional append happens
# right after the main `target_link_options(... -exported_symbols_list ...)`
# block on Apple.
#
# pass2-syn-002 split: previously all 9 backend-conditional symbols were
# silently omitted from RACommons.exports and tracked only by a comment
# block. The split makes the omission explicit and toggleable from the
# CMake flag that gates the backend.

# rac_rag_* proto-byte ABI (commons-side RAG pipeline entry points).
_rac_rag_clear_proto
_rac_rag_cancel_proto
_rac_rag_ingest_proto
_rac_rag_query_proto
_rac_rag_session_create_proto
_rac_rag_session_destroy_proto
_rac_rag_stats_proto

# rac_backend_rag_* — RAG backend plugin registration (publishes the engine
# vtable to the plugin registry; reached by SDK bridges at module-load time).
_rac_backend_rag_register
_rac_backend_rag_unregister
